\alpha \otimes (\beta + \gamma) = \alpha \otimes \beta + \alpha \otimes \gamma
V
 \alpha \otimes \beta (x,y) = \alpha(x)\beta(y) 
 \begin{align} \alpha \otimes (\beta + \gamma)(x,y)  &= \alpha(x)(\beta + \gamma)(y) \\ &= \alpha(x)[\beta(y) + \gamma(y)] \\ &= \alpha(x)\beta(y) + \alpha(x)\gamma(y) \\ &= \alpha \otimes \beta(x,y) + \alpha \otimes\gamma(x,y) \\ &= (\alpha \otimes \beta + \alpha \otimes\gamma)(x,y). \\ \end{align} 
